3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper proposes a novel channel model for cognitive radio communication, which is a topic within communication and networking. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper considers the use of cognitive radio for improving system performance, which is a topic within systems and control. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although the paper does not explicitly discuss security, cognitive radio systems have implications for security and could potentially fall under the domain of cryptography and security.
